  "prompt": "How long can I stay outside the UK as a dependant of the tier2 visa?",
  "response": "As a dependant of a Tier 2 visa holder in the UK, you can generally stay outside the UK for up to 2 years without losing your dependent status. However, if you are absent for more than 2 years, you may lose your right to return to the UK as a dependant. \n\nIt's important to ensure that your stay outside the UK does not affect your ability to apply for indefinite leave to remain (ILR) if that is your goal. If you have further questions or are in a specific situation, it's advisable to consult with an immigration lawyer or the UK Home Office for the most accurate and personalized advice.",
